    },
    {
      "text": "GT Advance 2: Rally Racing is a rally racing game developed by MTO and published by THQ for the Game Boy Advance, as a sequel to GT Advance Championship Racing. The game features cars from several real Japanese car manufacturers. The player can race on fourteen different courses located in various parts of the world or act as the co-driver. The game was released in Japan on the on December 7, 2001, and in North America and Europe in June 2002. It received generally favorable reviews from critics.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
    {
      "text": "GT Advance 2: Rally Racing (Advance Rally au Japon) est un jeu vidéo de course développé par MTO et édité par THQ, sorti en 2001 sur Game Boy Advance.",
      "lang": "fr",
      "source": "wikipedia_fr"
    },
    {
      "text": "GT Advance 2: Rally Racing, conocido en Japón como Advance Rally (アドバンスラリー, Adobansu Rarī?), es un videojuego de carreras de rally desarrollado por MTO y publicado por THQ para Game Boy Advance. Es la secuela de GT Advance Championship Racing.",
      "lang": "es",
      "source": "wikipedia_es"
    },
    {
      "text": "GT Advance 2: Rally Racing (conhecido como Advance Rally no Japão) é um jogo de corrida de rally  desenvolvido por MTO e publicado pela THQ para o Game Boy Advance. Ele foi lançado no Japão em 7 de dezembro de 2001, na Europa em 28 de junho de 2002, e na América do Norte em 30 de junho de 2002. Ele é a continuação do GT Advance Championship Racing",
      "lang": "pt",
      "source": "wikipedia_pt"
    },
    {
      "text": "『GT Advance 2: Rally Racing』は、MTOが開発し、THQが発売したゲームボーイアドバンス用ラリーレーシングゲームで、『GT Advance Championship Racing』の続編にあたります。本ゲームでは、複数の実在する日本の自動車メーカーの車がフィーチャーされています。プレイヤーは、世界各地に点在する14の異なるコースでレースに挑むほか、副操縦士としてプレイすることも可能です。日本国内では2001年12月7日に発売され、北米およびヨーロッパでは2002年6月に発売されました。批評家からは概ね好意的な評価を受けました。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "ai_local_gemma4",
      "base_lang": "en"
    }
  ]
